>filler right out there in the elements. The filler still seems to be 
>smooth enough, and I am wondering if i can dry this stuff out under some 
>heat lamps or something for a couple of weeks and then just sand it, prime 
>it and paint it. OR should I go through the trouble of trying to remove 
>all the old filler and then put new stuff on. Some considerations: I KNOW 
>that it would be best to just replace the whole nose clip with good 
>straight metal but I ain't gonna! Also, I am by no means doing a 
>professional resto I just want to fix this bus up to the point where it is 
>presentable and can be driven regularly. I will be !
>painting it myself, and I would like the paint to last at least for a 
>couple of years on this area. So what do y'all think, scrape out the old 
>and re-fill? or Sand it, prime it, paint it, and drive it?!
